<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <p xml:id="PN313-intro">tiṇai, atu; tuṟai, vallāṇmullai. māṅkuṭikiḻār.
      </p>
      <p xml:lang="en">  
      </p>
    </div>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="PN313">
<l>atta naṇṇiya nāṭukeḻu peruviṟal</l>
<l>kaipporuḷ yātoṉṟu milaṉē naccik</l>
<l>kāṇiya ceṉṟa viravaṉ mākkaḷ</l>
<l>kaḷiṟoṭu neṭuntēr vēṇṭiṉuṅ kaṭava</l>
<l>vuppoy cākāṭ ṭumaṇar kāṭṭak</l>
<l>kaḻimuri kuṉṟat taṟṟē</l>
<l>yeḷḷamai viṉṟava ṉuḷḷiya poruḷē.</l>
</lg>
<lg xml:lang="en">
<l>The man of great victories with a land that is located near the road</l>
<l>is without any object of wealth in [his] hand. When mendicant folks, who desirously </l>
<l>come to see him, ask [him for gifts], even if they want a large chariot with a bull  elephant,</l>
<l>when salt merchants with a cart loaded with salt show up,</l>
<l>[wealth] is like a hill eroded by the backwaters,</l>
<l>the wealth he considers is something free from reproach. </l>
</lg>
    </div>
  </body>
